	<h1>Using RStudio Efficiently to Optimize Analysis Workflow</h1>
	<h3 style="justify-content: flex-end;">April 20th, 2019</h3>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col space">
      <div class="title">
	<p>One thing I've noticed as a statistics student is how time consuming and repetitive data analysis can be. All of my analysis is done in RStudio, objectively the best gosh darn R IDE available. There are so many different tools that RStudio offers that are widely customizeable, ranging from code snippets, RMarkdown templates, and even personal R packages. However, I've noticed a huge trend among my fellow classmates that no one really takes advantage of these tools, making their analyses take much longer than they need to.</p>
